metadata.name: Forest Sunrise
metadata.description:
At Sunrise, through the forest, the gums illuminate,  
silently, the suns rays begin to penetrate.  
The trunks warm and shine, this view, forever mine,  
for nobody is there to even care, except me and a lone honey bee.

This gathering of tall, thin gum tree's caught my eye as I passed them by, making me stop to enjoy the sun on their trunks.

Intentional Camera Movement (ICM) involves the movement of the camera at a specific speed and/or direction during the operation of the shutter, resulting in a blurred image that still contains detail and a story of what it is about, and what it contains.
